														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1925631">
									

<p>+1</p>
<p>wowwee. I liked it. A couple of _minor_ quirky issues, but mostly good. I especially liked</p>
<blockquote>
<p>never hold sticks</p>
</blockquote>
<p>and the janitor's cleanup method. And the recurring hats.</p>
<p>Not sure how I feel about the Sculptor being behind it all, especially being possibly behind The Critic's execution. For me, I was 1000% SURE that</p>
<blockquote>
<p>What was the reason for killing The Critic? To spite Ruiz, perhaps.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Pico killed The Critic to Spite Ruiz. That was so obvious to me. I figured it was 100% obvious to Ruiz, as well. I didn't think there was any question or any other possible motive. I mean why would the Sculptor care to assassinate the Critic if Ruiz was 1 second away from doing it for him? From where I'm at, I like _that_ implication better, that the Scluptor was planning on Ruiz killing the Critic, but that Pico got excited and killed the Critic anyway just to spite Ruiz and ruin his moment of triumph.</p>

							</div>

								
